      <!-- Signed Requests -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-[var(--color-muted)]">Step 3</span>
        <div class="flex-1 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-24">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Signed requests — how agents prove who they are</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-16">
          <div class="lg:flex-1">
            <div class="overview-prose max-w-xl mb-8">
              <p>Once registered, every request the agent makes carries a short-lived JWT (60-second TTL) signed with the agent's private key. The server verifies the signature against the agent's stored public key, checks the agent's status and permissions, and processes the call.</p>
              <p>There are no refresh tokens and no long-lived sessions. The agent signs a new JWT for every request. If a token is intercepted, it's already expired by the time anyone could reuse it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="lg:w-[440px] xl:w-[480px] shrink-0">
            <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)]">
              <div class="px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-surface)] text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)]">What happens on every request</div>
              <div class="p-5 text-[11px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-muted)] space-y-3">
                <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-fg)] shrink-0 w-4 text-right">1</span>
                  <span>Agent asks host to sign a JWT</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-fg)] shrink-0 w-4 text-right">2</span>
                  <div>
