      </div>

      <!-- Modes -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-[var(--color-muted)]">Agent modes</span>
        <div class="flex-1 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-24">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Two agent modes</h2>
        <p class="text-[15px] text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-[1.85] font-[family-name:var(--font-serif)] max-w-2xl mb-10">The mode is chosen at registration and is immutable after creation. It determines how capabilities get approved and whether a user is in the loop.</p>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-[var(--color-border)] border border-[var(--color-border)]">
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-bg)] p-6 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
              <span class="text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] px-2 py-0.5 border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-muted)]">DEFAULT</span>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">Delegated</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="overview-prose !text-[13px] !leading-relaxed mb-5">
              <p>The agent acts on behalf of a specific user. The user sees what the agent is requesting and decides what to allow. When the agent needs more permissions, the user approves through the same device flow used for registration.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[11px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-muted)] space-y-1">
              <div>→ Copilots & assistants</div>
              <div>→ Tool-calling agents in Cursor / Claude</div>
              <div>→ User-facing automations</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-bg)] p-6 sm:p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold">Autonomous</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="overview-prose !text-[13px] !leading-relaxed mb-5">
              <p>The agent operates without a user in the loop. Capabilities are granted by server policy or administrator approval. If the host is later linked to a user, autonomous agents are claimed — their work is attributed to that user and the agents are archived.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="text-[11px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-muted)] space-y-1">
              <div>→ Background workers</div>
              <div>→ Scheduled automations</div>
              <div>→ Service-to-service agents</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Lifecycle -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-[var(--color-muted)]">Lifecycle</span>
        <div class="flex-1 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-24">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Agent states and lifetime</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-16">
          <div class="lg:flex-1">
            <div class="overview-prose max-w-xl mb-8">
              <p>Every agent moves through a defined set of states. Only <strong>active</strong> agents can authenticate. Three independent clocks govern expiry — the server sets the durations based on its own policy.</p>
              <p>An expired agent can be reactivated, but reactivation is a security checkpoint: escalated capabilities are dropped and must be re-requested. A revoked agent cannot be reactivated.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)]">
              <div class="px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-surface)] text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)]">Lifetime clocks</div>
              <div class="p-5 text-[12px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-muted)]">
                <div><span class="text-[var(--color-fg)]">Session TTL</span> — measured from last request. Agent expires if idle too long.</div>
                <div><span class="text-[var(--color-fg)]">Max lifetime</span> — measured from last activation. Caps continuous use even for active agents.</div>
                <div><span class="text-[var(--color-fg)]">Absolute lifetime</span> — measured from creation. Hard cap, never resets, no reactivation.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="lg:w-[380px] xl:w-[420px] shrink-0">
            <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)]">
              <div class="px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-surface)] text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)]">Agent states</div>
              <div class="p-5 space-y-2">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2.5 border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/5">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500 shrink-0"></span>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-[12px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-fg)]">pending</div>
                    <div class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-muted)]">Waiting for user to approve</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2.5 border border-green-500/20 bg-green-500/5">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500 shrink-0"></span>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-[12px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-fg)]">active</div>
                    <div class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-muted)]">Operational — can make requests</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2.5 border border-[var(--color-border)]">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-muted)] shrink-0"></span>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-[12px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-fg)]">expired</div>
                    <div class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-muted)]">Timed out — can be reactivated</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 p-2.5 border border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-red-500 shrink-0"></span>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-[12px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-fg)]">revoked</div>
                    <div class="text-[10px] text-[var(--color-muted)]">Permanently killed — start over</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparisons -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-[var(--color-muted)]">Comparison</span>
        <div class="flex-1 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-24">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Relationship to existing standards</h2>
        <p class="text-[15px] text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-[1.85] font-[family-name:var(--font-serif)] max-w-2xl mb-10">Agent Auth is not a replacement for OAuth, API keys, or MCP. It addresses a specific gap — agent identity — that sits between the user and the service.</p>

        <div class="border border-[var(--color-border)] overflow-hidden">
          <table class="w-full text-[12px] border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-[var(--color-surface)]">
                <th class="text-left px-4 sm:px-5 py-3 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] border-b border-[var(--color-border)]"></th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 sm:px-5 py-3 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">What it does</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 sm:px-5 py-3 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">What it's missing</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 sm:px-5 py-3 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] border-b border-[var(--color-border)] hidden sm:table-cell">Works together?</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">
              <tr class="border-b border-[color-mix(in_oklch,var(--color-fg)_5%,transparent)]">
                <td class="px-4 sm:px-5 py-3 text-[var(--color-fg)] font-medium whitespace-nowrap">OAuth 2.0</td>
                <td class="px-4 sm:px-5 py-3">Authorizes apps to act for users</td>
                <td class="px-4 sm:px-5 py-3">Can't distinguish between agents sharing a token</td>
                <td class="px-4 sm:px-5 py-3 hidden sm:table-cell text-green-500">Yes — uses OAuth's device flow</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[color-mix(in_oklch,var(--color-fg)_5%,transparent)]">
                <td class="px-4 sm:px-5 py-3 text-[var(--color-fg)] font-medium whitespace-nowrap">API Keys</td>
                <td class="px-4 sm:px-5 py-3">Static credentials for access</td>
                <td class="px-4 sm:px-5 py-3">No per-agent identity, scoping, or lifecycle</td>
                <td class="px-4 sm:px-5 py-3 hidden sm:table-cell text-green-500">Replaces static keys</td>
              </tr>
